REPORT DATE:    20 March 2009 [provided to CIA by Pakistani Criminal Investigation Unit, Karachi Division]NOTE:  Surveillance report on the activities of Akram Basra, suspected to be an associate of a top leader within the Karachi faction of Lashkar-e-Jhangvi.  Basra is frequently accompanied by Maulana Haq Bukhari, and acts as his driver and bodyguard.  Additional information provided by police informants. 3 January 2009:  Basra was followed from his Bihar Colony apartment (near Lyari Town in Karachi) to a house on Moosa Lane.  He entered through a side door without knocking.  He stayed about 20 minutes, exited through a back door and left on foot to Nawab MahabatKhangi Road where he hired a taxi.3 January 2009:  A contact at Allama Iqbal International Airport reports Basra paid cash for three tickets on Emirates Airlines from Karachi to Dubai for 18 April 2009, returning to Karachi on 20 April 2009.